                  <h3>Whether contribution to EPF mandatory ? </h3>
                  <p>For those who have a basic salary up to Rs. 6500, contributing to the EPF is mandatory. Contributions are voluntary for those whose basic salary exceeds Rs. 6,500. However, it is strongly recommended to make such contributions to avail of the various benefits an EPF account has.</p>
                  <p>
                    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#section-html5-css3">Where does my monthly EPF contribution go ? </a>
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="tab-pane" id="cntb">
                  <br>
                  <h3>An employee's monthly contribution would go into the following three schemes </h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>EPF (Employees Provident Fund Act 1952) : 15.67 % Of Monthly Wages</ii>
                    <li>EPS (Employees' Pension Scheme), 1995 : 8.33 % of Monthly Wages</li>
                    <li>EDLIS (Employees' Deposit Linked Insurance Scheme 1976) : 0.5 % of Monthly Wages</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    <a class="btn" href="#section-html5-css3">View details</a>
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="tab-pane" id="withdrawal">
                  <br>
                  <h3>For Education, Marriage, Purchase of a house, Medical emergencies.</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <p>Purposes: Children's education, Marriage of self/children/siblings, Purchase/construction of a house, Medical emergencies.</p>
                    <li>Should have completed minimum seven years of service.</li>
                    <li>Withdrawal can be made only three times in the period during which you hold the EPF account</li>
                    <li>Maximum aggregate withdrawal would be 50 per cent of the total contributions made by you.</li>
                    <li>For medical emergencies, there is no minimum service period. However, the maximum amount one can withdraw is six times the basic salary and proof of hospitalization is required.</li>
                    <li>Withdrawal from EPF account for purchase/construction of a house is available only once in an individual's entire working life. The minimum service period is five years and the maximum withdrawal amount is 36 times your total salary (for construction of property) and 24 times (for purchase of property).</li>
                    <li>Withdrawal is subject to certain conditions, non-compliance of which would result in penal interest.</li>
                  </ul>
