                  <h3>Change or Quit a Job without joining elsewhere</h3>
                  <p>What to do when you change job? What should be done if you quit job without joining elsewhere? </p>
                  <p>At such times, the PF balance could be transferred from one employer to another. The existing balance would continue to stay, with fresh contributions made by the new employer. When you quit your job, the PF could be withdrawn. You need to provide a declaration that you do not intend to work for the next six months.</p>
