        <section class="section-content section-contribution-accounts" id="section-contribution-accounts">
          <h3 class="section-title">
            Where Your Contribution Goes?
            <small>accounting of Employee and Employer contributions</small>
          </h3>
          <p>All salaried individuals working in organizations registered under the Employees Provident Fund Organization, contribute @ 12 % of drawn monthly wages to their Employees’ Provident Fund (EPF). This contribution in full goes straight to Employees PF Account. Employer also make a monthly contribution which is splitted into Three Basic Categories.</p>
          <p> First is <strong>Employees' Provident Fund Contribution ( EPF )</strong></p>
          <p> Second is <strong>Employees' Pension Scheme Contibution ( EPS )</strong></p>
          <p> Third is <strong>Employees' Deposit Linked Insurance Scheme Contribution ( EDLIS )</strong></p>
          <p><strong> Break-up of Total Contribution</strong></p>
          <p><strong>Employee ' Contribution: </strong> Deducted from Monthly wages / salary </p>
          <p>12% (of Basic + Dearness Allowance) into EPF .</p>

          <p><strong>Employer' Contribution :</strong> Calculated on monthly wages/salry (Basic +Dearness Allowance) - fully borne by employer</p>
          <p>3.67% into EPF</p>
          <p>8.33% into EPS</p>
          <p>0.5% into EDLIS</p>
          <p>1.1% for EPF Administrative Charges</p>
          <p>0.01% for EDLIS Administrative Charges</p>
        </section>

