        <section class="section-content section-pension-amount" id="section-pension-amount">
          <h3 class="section-title">
            Pension Amount
            <small>for those who have joined EPF after 15.11.95</small>
          </h3>
          <p>A member who has joined EPF Scheme AFTER 15.11.1995 will get EITHER Pension OR Pensionable Service Benefits - as the case may be.</p>
                                <pre><p>The formula of calculation of pension is similar to that of a Govt.Employee.</p>
                                     <p>Average Salary   X   Service Years Divided by 70</p>
                                     <p>Maximum service for the calculation of service is 35 yrs. If a member has maximum service, pension will be - Average Salary divided by 2</p>
                                     <p>The Average Salary is named as pensionable salary in the scheme. It is arrived by considering the average contributing salary preceding 12 months from the date of exit.</p></pre>

          <p>If no wage is earned for a certain period, that period is to be deducted from the service (as there will be no contribution to Pension Fund) </p>
        </section>

