          <h3 class="section-title">
            Withdrawal Benefits
            <small>align everything</small>
          </h3>
          <p>If your total service is less than 9.5 years, you can apply for Pension Fund Money back (Withdrawal benefit). As you are not entitled for pension, you may withdraw the deposit amounts. </p>
                                <pre><p>The Withdrawal benefit calculation (as in the case of Pension Calculation) is depending on Average salary and total service,</p>
                                     <p>It is NOT related to your actual Balance in Pension Fund.</p></pre>
          <p>EPF Pension scheme is very liberal insurance to your life after job.In case you die before 58 years of age after contributing to EPF Pension scheme for at least 1 year, your family is entitled for Pension. </p>
          <p>You can add services at different companies by applying for Scheme certificate, and if your total service is at least 10 years, you can get pension from the age of 50 years on wards.</p>
